webpackJsonp([0xd0c138a6a769],{473:function(e,a){e.exports={data:{wordpressWpLessons:{id:"5667fc9b-3f4d-5c36-beff-aa5390e017e2",wordpress_id:6088,title:"Tinkercad: Design a Model of a Landmark",slug:"tinkercad-design-model-landmark",content:'<h2>Activity Overview</h2>\n<p>For this activity, we will be using the Design Process to create a model of a Baltimore Landmark. Creating models is a critical skill for many designers from engineers and architects to sculptors and set designers. We will be manipulating the scale of Baltimore landmarks and, if necessary, implementing modular assembly.</p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-6089" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="359" srcset="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD.jpg 500w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD-300x215.jpg 300w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD-139x100.jpg 139w, http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnollMD-100x72.jpg 100w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /></a></p>\n<p><a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnoll_Tinkercad.png"><img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-6090" src="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/10/SevenFtKnoll_Tinkercad-300x169.png" alt="" width="500" height="359" /></a></p>\n<h2><strong><span style="color: #0091c9;">Activity: Design a Model of a Landmark</span></strong></h2>\n<ol>\n<li style="list-style-type: none;">\n<ul>\n<li>First, choose a landmark to model. This can be one of the landmarks provided by program staff or one of your choosing (for example, you may choose to make a scaled-down model of your own house)</li>\n<li>Create a prototype of your model using play-doh or legos</li>\n<li>Design your model in Tinkercad. Keep your design within 70 x 70 x 70 mm. If you find these parameters difficult to work within, you may create your design in multiple parts &#8211; manufacturers call this process modular assembly.</li>\n<li>Name your design and upload to Fabhive following the steps outlined in <a href="http://learn.digitalharbor.org/lesson/tinkercad-make-a-custom-keychain/">Tinkercad: Make a Custom Keychain</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n'}},pathContext:{}}}});
